sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor U as User
    participant R as Renderer (React UI, sandboxed)
    participant M as Main Process (Electron / Node)
    participant FS as Local Encrypted Storage (orgs.json)
    participant SF as Customer Salesforce Org
    participant API as Jetstream Server

    Note over U,API: Orgs are stored on the user's computer, encrypted with the<br/>user-derived key (delivered by the server at login; held in memory).

    rect rgb(232, 240, 254)
    Note over U,SF: Salesforce data path - desktop <-> Salesforce (DIRECT)
    U->>R: Run query / action
    R->>M: IPC request (via contextBridge; renderer never sees tokens)
    M->>FS: Read org; file is AES-256-GCM ("JSEK" + IV + authTag)
    M->>M: Decrypt token (jsek: blob) with in-memory user-derived key
    M->>M: Build ApiConnection (Bearer = access token)
    M->>SF: HTTPS {instanceUrl}/services/data/... (Bearer token, same-origin pinned)
    SF-->>M: Salesforce records
    M-->>R: IPC response
    Note over M,SF: fetch runs in the Node main process, straight to Salesforce.<br/>On 401, refresh directly with Salesforce, re-encrypt locally.
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
    Note over M,API: Jetstream server - control plane only (NO Salesforce data)
    M->>API: /desktop-app/auth/verify - session, entitlement, encryption key, JWT rotation
    opt If user enables record-history sync
        M->>API: /desktop-app/data-sync (saved queries / history metadata)
    end
    end

    Note over U,API: Salesforce credentials and record data stay on the device /<br/>go direct to Salesforce - never stored on Jetstream servers.
